claim.claim-text:
A dynamic characteristic calculation apparatus calculating dynamic characteristic of a machine tool to execute an interrupted machining by moving relative to a workpiece a rotational tool having one or plural tool tips comprising;

a detector detecting acoustic wave generated by vibration of said rotational tool or detecting magnetic property being variable by said vibration of said rotational tool where said rotational tool is excited to vibrate; and

a calculation division calculating a natural frequency of said one or plural tool tips in a vibration system, in which said one or plural tool tips of said rotational tool is a vibration body, on a basis of a value detected by said detector.

A dynamic characteristic calculation apparatus according to Claim 1, wherein;

said machine tool includes a driving device moving said rotational tool relative to said workpiece; and

said rotational tool is excited to vibrate by contacting said rotational tool with a target member mounted on said machine tool by driving said driving device.

A dynamic characteristic calculation apparatus according to Claim 4, wherein;

said rotational tool is mounted on a tool holder fixed on a spindle of said machine tool;

said rotational tool includes said one or plural tool tips at a top side, and a non-tip portion at a base side; and

said rotational tool is excited to vibrate by contacting said non-tip portion of said rotational tool with said target member by driving said driving device.

A dynamic characteristic calculation apparatus according to Claim 1, wherein;

said dynamic characteristic of said one or plural tool tips includes said natural frequency and a mass coefficient in said vibration system; and

said dynamic characteristic calculation apparatus includes a FEM analysis division obtaining said mass coefficient by executing FEM analysis based on constructional information of said machine tool.

A dynamic characteristic calculation apparatus according to Claim 8, wherein;

said FEM analysis division obtains said natural frequency by executing FEM analysis;

said detector detects said acoustic wave or said magnetic property in detecting condition decided on a basis of said natural frequency obtained by said FEM analysis division; and

said calculation division calculates said natural frequency on a basis of said detected value by said detector, replaces said natural frequency obtained by said FEM analysis division to said calculated natural frequency based on said detected value by said detector, and registers said replaced natural frequency.

A dynamic characteristic calculation apparatus according to Claim 9, wherein;

said dynamic characteristic includes damping ratio in said vibration system; and

said calculation division calculates said damping ratio on a basis of said detected value by said detector.

A dynamic characteristic calculation apparatus according to Claim 8, wherein;

said dynamic characteristic of said one or plural tool tips includes damping ratio in said vibration system; and

said FEM analysis division obtains said damping ratio by executing FEM analysis.

A method of a dynamic characteristic calculation calculating dynamic characteristic of a machine tool to execute an interrupted machining by moving relative to a workpiece a rotational tool having one or plural tool tips comprising steps of;

detecting acoustic wave generated by vibration of said rotational tool or detecting magnetic property being variable by said vibration of said rotational tool where said rotational tool is excited to vibrate; and

calculating a natural frequency of said one or plural tool tips in a vibration system, in which said one or plural tool tips of said rotational tool is a vibration body, on a basis of a value detected in said detecting step.

A method of a dynamic characteristic calculation calculating dynamic characteristic of a machine tool to execute an interrupted machining by moving relative to a workpiece a rotational tool having one or plural tool tips comprising steps of;

said dynamic characteristic of said one or plural tool tips includes a mass coefficient and a natural frequency in a vibration system in which said one or plural tool tips of said rotational tool is a vibration body;

obtaining said mass coefficient by executing FEM analysis based on constructional information of said machine tool;

detecting acoustic wave generated by vibration of said rotational tool or detecting magnetic property being variable by said vibration of said rotational tool where said rotational tool is excited to vibrate; and

calculating said natural frequency on a basis of a value detected in said detecting step.

4. A method of a dynamic characteristic calculation calculating dynamic characteristic of a machine tool to execute an interrupted machining by moving relative to a workpiece (W) a rotational tool (6) having one or plural tool tips (6a, 6b), wherein

said dynamic characteristic of said one or plural tool tips (6a, 6b) includes a mass coefficient (M) and a natural frequency (f) in a vibration system in which said one or plural tool tips (6a, 6b) of said rotational tool (6) is a vibration body, characterized by comprising steps of:
obtaining said mass coefficient (M) by executing FEM analysis based on constructional information of said machine tool;
obtaining said natural frequency (f) by executing FEM analysis;
detecting acoustic wave generated by vibration of said rotational tool (6) or detecting magnetic property being variable by said vibration of said rotational tool (6) where said rotational tool (6) is excited to vibrate, in detecting condition decided on a basis of said natural frequency (f) obtained by said FEM analysis;
calculating said natural frequency (f) on a basis of a value detected in said detecting step;
replacing said natural frequency (f) obtained by said FEM analysis to said calculated natural frequency (f) based on the value detected in said detecting step, and registering said natural frequency (f).

7. Method according to Claim 4, wherein;

said machine tool includes a driving device (4) moving said rotational tool relative to said workpiece (W); and

said rotational tool (6) is excited to vibrate by contacting said rotational tool (6) with a target member mounted on said machine tool by driving said driving device (4).

9. Method according to Claim 4, wherein;

said rotational tool (6) is mounted on a tool holder (5) fixed on a spindle (4a) of said machine tool;

said rotational tool (6) includes said one or plural tool tips (6a, 6b) at a top side, and a non-tip portion (6c) at a base side; and

said rotational tool (6) is excited to vibrate by contacting said non-tip portion (6c) of said rotational tool (6) with said target member by driving said driving device (4).
